Tasmania is an island state of Australia. It is located 240 km to the south of the Australian mainland#Comma separated by the Bass Strait.

This national park offers excellent bushwalking#Comma fishing and wildlife viewing of the island's more than 80 species of birds and native animals#Comma including emus and wallabies that are frequently sighted.

Yarns Artwork in Silk is a unique 3D textile art installation consisting of 4 very large handworked silk panels decipting local events and vistas in a seasonal diaroma.

Indulging in succulent milk-fed lamb at Tasmania’s best restaurants is a decadent experience#Comma but visiting the island where it was produced and cooking it on a beachside BBQ? Freshness and fun guaranteed!

They may be exported by the pallet load but Tasmania’s famous National pies are best eaten straight from the oven. Made from Cape Grim beef#Comma you can grab one of these sensational savory treats fresh from Tasmanian Bakeries’ renowned Hobart bakery.

Tasmania is famous for the quality of its butter#Comma and Fudgey takes this superb ingredient and blends it with chocolate to make one of the island’s most indulgent and delicious treats. Witness the masters at work in the Eaglehawk Neck store before indulging.
Leatherwood honey is exclusive to the wilderness surrounding Cradle Mountain. When you’ve finished exploring#Comma make a stop in Mole Creek where you can buy it from the factory door.
